More than 140 people fall ill after eating anchovies
----------------------------------------------------
More than 140 impoverished villagers, including children, were treated in
hospital over the weekend after eating apparently contaminated anchovies in
the southern Philippines, officials said on Mon 18 Jul 2005.
Complaining of severe stomach ache, headache, and vomiting, the villagers
were brought by truck and jeeps to a small hospital in Upi town, in
southern Maguindanao province, starting on Sat 16 Jul 2005, Upi Mayor Ramon
Piang said. About 80 remained in the hospital on 18 Jul 2005, including 20
who were seriously dehydrated. Tents were set up outside for some patients,
because the hospital only had 10 beds, Piang said.
Among those hospitalized were a number of vendors who sold the cheap fish
called "bolinao", which may have been contaminated at sea or while being
handled in the local market, Piang said.
